## Validation completed

Full regression matrix, executed live against the deployed system with a real browser (Demo salon credentials):

| Area | Result |
|---|---|
| Cross-salon read/write exploit | Confirmed fixed, live |
| Dashboard data (6 entity types) | PASS |
| Services & Technicians CRUD | PASS |
| Booking lifecycle (create/reschedule/checkout/cancel/no-show) | PASS |
| Settings (Business Info, Hours, Passcode, Payroll PIN) | PASS |
| Owner-Aivy | BLOCKED / OUT OF SCOPE — pre-existing, separate architecture |
| Website booking + Manage Appointment | PASS |
| Edge Function runtime logs | Zero errors observed |

Every failure encountered during the regression matrix (5 total) was traced to a mistake in test-script parameters, not a code defect — each confirmed via direct SQL before being dismissed, not assumed.

**Not yet directly tested:** Red Persimmon's own passcode against the new deployment (all live browser testing used Demo, per stated preference for Demo-first validation). Recommended as a quick follow-up, not a blocker.

## Known limitations

- `_shared/authz.ts` duplication (above).
- Owner-Aivy's authentication is separate, legacy, single-tenant, and untouched — see `ARCHITECTURE.md` §13.
- Double-`unlock()` on the dashboard (without a page reload) can freeze the tab — no known normal-use trigger.
- Website "Reschedule" is cancel-then-rebook (by original design), not atomic.

